The paper deals with the construction of testers for sets of functions, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of algebraic function fields suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper mentions applications to hitting sets and cover-free families, which are topics in computational geometry (cs.CG).
